 <sect1 id="sec.user.docupdate.cloud3.maint1">
  <title>February 24, 2014 (Maintenance Release &productname; 3)</title>
  <!--state if new or updated, if applicable, add number of bug, fate,
   or doc comment for reference-->
  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Image Management</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>Added a note to highlight
        the importance of setting image properties, especially when using mixed
        virtualization environments. See <xref linkend="sec.user.dash.img"/>.</para></listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>Slightly reorganized <xref
         linkend="sec.user.dash.img"/>. Added more subsections for quicker
        overview.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>Shortened <xref linkend="sec.user.cli.img"/>. Referred to <xref
         linkend="sec.adm.cli.img"/> for detailed information.</para></listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
 </variablelist>
 </sect1>
 <sect1 id="sec.user.docupdate.cloud3.gm">
  <title>February 17, 2014 (Initial Release &productname; 3)</title>
  <!--state if new or updated, if applicable, add number of bug, fate,
   or doc comment for reference-->
  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Update to &ostack; Havana</term>
    <listitem>
     <para> The &dash; and the command line chapter have been updated to the
      &ostack; Havana release on which &productname; 3 is based. This
      includes the following changes: </para>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>All screenshots have been updated.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para> Some categories have been added to the &dash;'s main screen,
        resulting in an update of the following section: <xref
         linkend="sec.adm.dash.intro.main"/>. </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para><xref linkend="sec.user.dash.inst.launch"/> and <xref
         linkend="sec.user.cli.inst.launch"/> have been split into subsections
        about launching instances from images, from volumes, or from
        snapshots.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>The &productname; &dash; now provides templates for some
        commonly-used security group rules, see <xref
         linkend="pro.cloud.dash.security.rules"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>Added the section <xref linkend="sec.user.dash.inst.manage.resize"
        />.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>Adjusted the workflow for the following tasks: <xref
         linkend="pro.user.dash.img.upload"/> and <xref
         linkend="pro.user.dash.vol.create"/>. </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>Reflected package name change from <systemitem class="resource"
         >python-quantumclient</systemitem> to <systemitem class="resource"
         >python-neutronclient</systemitem>.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>Added admonition that specifying an arbitrary image is needed when
        booting from volumes, see <xref
         linkend="pro.user.cli.instances.launch.vol"/>.</para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>High-level User Roles</term>
    <listitem>
     <para> Added definition of user roles to <xref linkend="pre.cloud.user"/>.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="sec.user.cli.inst.manage"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <para> Added new section to <xref linkend="cha.user.cli"/>. </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="sec.user.cli.volumes"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <para> Added new section to <xref linkend="cha.user.cli"/>. </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Offline and Live Migration of Instances</term>
    <listitem>
     <para> If a &compnode; needs to be shut down (for example, for a
      maintenance update), instances running on the &compnode; need to be
      migrated to another node. For details, refer to <xref
       linkend="sec.user.dash.migrate"/> and <xref linkend="sec.adm.cli.migrate"
      />. </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        <xref linkend="sec.user.dash.inst.manage.snapshots"/>: Added note about
        how to remove former keypairs from an instance&mdash;either for
        preparing a snapshot (<ulink
         url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=839364"/>) or for
        changing the keypairs in a running instance <ulink
         url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=839721"/>). </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
