 <sect1 id="sec.user.docupdate.cloud2.maint1">
  <title>September 25, 2013 (Maintenance Release &productname; 2.0)</title>
  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Managing Networks</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added a section about managing networks to
        <xref
        linkend="cha.user.cli"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        <xref linkend="sec.user.dash.networks"/> has been enhanced.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        <xref linkend="sec.user.dash.inst.access.keys"
        xrefstyle="select:title"/>:
        For accessing an instance via SSH from a Windows* machine, the keys
        need to be converted
        (<ulink
        url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=838908"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
 <sect1 id="sec.user.docupdate.cloud2.gm">
  <title>September 11, 2013 (Initial Release &productname; 2.0)</title>

  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>&ostack; Service Names</term>
    <listitem>
<!--state if new or updated, if applicable, add number of bug, fate,
      or doc comment for reference-->
     <para>
      Replaced code names with the &ostack; services' real names, according
      to
      <ulink
        url="https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/Conventions#General_style_conventions"
       />.
      For example, talk of <emphasis>&ostack; &img;</emphasis> instead of
      <emphasis>&o_img;</emphasis>.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Update to &ostack; Grizzly</term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      The &dash; and the command line chapter have been updated to the
      &ostack; Grizzly release on which &productname; 2.0 is based. This
      includes the following changes:
     </para>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added the following section:
        <xref
          linkend="sec.user.dash.networks"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Some categories have been added to the &dash;'s main screen, others
        changed name. Most importantly, the download option for RC files can
        now be found in the <guimenu>Access &amp; Security</guimenu>
        category. See <xref linkend="sec.user.dash.intro"/> and
        <xref
          linkend="sec.user.cli.rc"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Image upload is now also possible via the &dash;, though with
        limited options. For details, refer to
        <xref
          linkend="sec.user.dash.img"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The workflow for some tasks has changed, most notably for the
        following ones: <xref linkend="sec.user.dash.inst.launch"/>,
        <xref
          linkend="pro.cloud.dash.security.rules"/>,
        <xref
          linkend="pro.user.dash.assign.floating.ips"/>, and
        <xref
          linkend="pro.user.dash.vol.attach"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        On the command line, managing security groups, security group rules,
        and IP addresses can now also be done with the
        <command>neutron</command> commands, provided by the
        <systemitem
          class="resource">python-quantumclient</systemitem>
        package. For details, see
        <xref linkend="sec.user.cli.inst.access.security"/> and
        <xref linkend="sec.user.cli.inst.access.ips"/>. However, the former
        way of executing these tasks with the <command>nova</command> python
        client is also still supported.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
